Class MapMessage<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • madkit.kernel.Message
      • madkit.message.ObjectMessage<Map<K,V>>
        • madkit.message.MapMessage<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable

    public class MapMessage<K,V>
extends ObjectMessage<Map<K,V>>
    This class could be used to build message conveying Map objects between MaDKit agents.

    MaDKit 5.1.2

    0.9

      • put

        public V put(K key,
             V value)
        invoke Map.put(Object, Object) on the map contained in this message.
        Parameters:
        key - key with which the specified value is to be associated
        value - value to be associated with the specified key
        Returns:
        the previous value associated with key, or null if there was no mapping for key. (A null return can also indicate that the map previously associated null with key, if the implementation supports null values.)

        Map
